712028f-a.title: Manhattan: 33rd Street (East) - 1st Avenue
712028f-a.text:
(1)
East 33rd St., west from 1st Avenue (right foreground) and
showing at the north west corner of same a gasoline station. Note
in the background the Empire Stato B1dS. at Fifth Ave.. Underneath
the street surface runs a tunnel of the ennsylvania Railroad,
connecting their terminal at 7th Ave. with Long Island.
March 27, 1938.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONs
(2)
A similar view from apoint of vantage between 1st and 2nd Aves.
Note at the right the Church and School of the Sacred Heart Roman
Catholic Church. The former bears No. 309-15 and the latter No. 317-23;
both east of 2ni Avenue.
May 8, 1938.
P. i. Sperr
NO REPRODCCTIONS.
(3)
A detail, showing Nos. 303 to 331 with the aforementioned Church
and School.
